<center><h1><b><u>FAQs</u></b></h1></center>
<h1><b>1. What am I going to develop ?</b></h1>
<p>You will be developing teaching kits in any platform that you are comfortable in-be it web
    development, android application , IoT ,etc. You can also ideate, and implement
    games/activities which can be used as a powerful tool for teaching.</p>
<h1><b>2. What are teaching kits ?</b></h1>
<p>Teaching kits are tools that can be used to make teaching simpler. That make a session more
    interesting for both the listener and the facilitator. They may include softwares, activities, games,
    anything that makes the way a concept is explained simple.</p>
<h1><b>3. What are some examples of teaching kits ?</b></h1>
<p>Check out the examples that can be found on our website
    <a href="https://learning.mozilla.org/en-US/activities" target="_blank">https://learning.mozilla.org/en-US/activities</a>
    Eg. MINECRAFT: Redesign a Public Sector is a game to foster civic engagement, self-efficacy
    and agency using the wildly popular video game, Minecraft.</p>
<h1><b>4. Is it necessary for teaching kits to be based on computer - related subjects?</b></h1>
<p>Teaching kits help make teaching simpler. There are no limitations on the subject matter. They must be capable of making teaching of a subject easier, the subject may or may not be related to computers.</p>
