<h1><b>6. What should be the size and composition of the team ?</b></h1>
<p>The team can consist of members of any year and any branch, but a maximum of 4 members only. Forming a team is not necessary and one can participate individually.</p>
<h1><b>7. What do we have to bring for the hackathon?</b></h1>
<p>Laptops is compulsory for every team. Atleast one laptop per team is compulsory. The laptops needs to be fully charged. If you are ideating any activity/game, you also have to bring other necessary items for demonstration purposes.</p>
<h1><b>8. So, what is the duration and breaks during the hackathon ?</b></h1>
<p>The hackathon will last  around 8 hrs with a 1hr official break for lunch from 1:30pm to 2:30 pm.</p>
<h1><b>9. Is it necessary to develop from scratch in the hackathon duration ?</b></h1>
<p>No, it is not necessary to develop from scratch on the spot.
    You may start from scratch or you may continue your partially developed projects.</p>
<h1><b>10. How will the candidates be judged?</b></h1>
<p>The participants will be judged on two criterias:
    a. Ideation Phase: 
                      This phase will mainly showcase the main idea. The participating team needs to explain their idea as a form a document stating their main idea and how you plan to implement the same,clearly.
    b.  Implementation Phase:
     The participating teams/individuals need to develop the app,software,web app, games/activities etc according to stated idea.The implementation aspect need not be developed from scratch but at the time of submission it should be a fully developed prototype.
    
    The participants will be required to submit their prototype and ideation documents ,both, at the starting of the event , which will be reviewed by the mentor Mr. Chad Sansing (Curriculum Designer,Mozilla)</p>
